#: ../../../topics/webservice.rst:7
msgid ""
"Scrapy comes with a built-in web service for monitoring and controlling a "
"running crawler. The service exposes most resources using the `JSON-RPC "
"2.0`_ protocol, but there are also other (read-only) resources which just "
"output JSON data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/webservice.rst:12
msgid ""
"Provides an extensible web service for managing a Scrapy process. It's "
"enabled by the :setting:`WEBSERVICE_ENABLED` setting. The web server will "
"listen in the port specified in :setting:`WEBSERVICE_PORT`, and will log to "
"the file specified in :setting:`WEBSERVICE_LOGFILE`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/webservice.rst:17
msgid ""
"The web service is a :ref:`built-in Scrapy extension <topics-extensions-"
"ref>` which comes enabled by default, but you can also disable it if you're "
"running tight on memory."
msgstr ""

